export const DESIGN_REFERENCES = "# KENT WEB DESIGN — DESIGN REFERENCES (the wow bar)\n> The standard we build to. Read alongside `MASTER-BUILD-PROMPT.md`.\n> These are the *level* to hit — never copy one wholesale (see the \"no two sites alike\" rule). Steal the *principles*, not the layout.\n\n## Reference sites (Jake-approved)\n| Site | Study it for |\n|---|---|\n| https://capeq.com/ | Premium, confident corporate feel — restraint, space, typography as the hero. |\n| https://www.ttp.com/ | **The hero section** specifically — how a high-end hero commands attention. |\n| `http://localhost:8137/index.html` | One of our own builds Jake rates \"very good\" — our current best; match or beat it. |\n| https://horizonroofingse.co.uk/ | A real UK roofing site — the trade-relevant benchmark to beat. |\n| Dribbble — \"Roofing website design landing page\" (shot 23998642) | The RoofGuard concept below — polished trade landing page. |\n\n## Design DNA — pulled from the two hero shots Jake loves\n**RoofGuard (roofing) + SunVault (solar) — the recurring winning patterns:**\n\n1. **Oversized display type as the centrepiece.** The trade word set HUGE — \"ROOFING\" / \"Solar Power\" spanning the hero, part of the art, often layered behind/over the image. Big, brave, confident. **Timid type is the enemy.**\n2. **A hero with real depth.** A strong photo (RoofGuard) or cinematic 3D render (SunVault) with clear foreground/background separation — subject overlaps the giant type. Not a flat banner.\n3. **Floating rounded/pill nav.** Clean top bar, pill-shaped, one highlighted active item, a solid accent-colour CTA button top-right (\"Contact Us\" / \"Get Started\").\n4. **One bold accent colour** doing all the work — RoofGuard orange, SunVault electric yellow — against a restrained/neutral or dark base. Palette pulled from the brand.\n5. **Dual hero CTA:** a primary (\"Get Your Free Estimate\" / \"Get Started\") + a **\"Call Now\"** pill. Ties straight to our calls goal.\n6. **Glassmorphic / floating cards** at the hero base — reviews (4.8★), product specs, feature callouts — layered over the image for depth.\n7. **Generous rounded corners, soft shadows, spec-callout pills** (\"SUN POWER\", \"50W\") anchored to the render. Premium, considered, never flat.\n8. **Cinematic mood** — SunVault's dark, moody, glowing render vs RoofGuard's bright airy sky. Either works; the drama and polish is the point.\n\n## How to apply (per build)\n- Pick the mood from the client's logo + trade, then **hit this level of hero ambition every time** — giant type, depth, one bold accent, dual CTA (incl. Call Now), floating glass cards.\n- **Go a different direction each client** (bright/airy vs dark/cinematic, photo vs render, different type personality) — same bar, distinct execution.\n- Use Lenis + GSAP to bring it alive (type reveal, image parallax, cards floating in on scroll); WebGL for a flagship hero render moment where it earns it.\n";
